Well last weekend was one for the books…Fish were caught, laughs were had, but most importantly memories were made! ❤️

A huge thank you to @thereddoorresort for having us, I couldn’t have imagined a more perfect meeting place for our large @dsgfish family! 

Here’s a short little recap of our incredible weekend, and if you ever have the chance #dothelake
Tell all the girls DSG has you covered for all seasons! ❤️

First time Burbot fishing… 😜😂
Happy Valentine’s Day ❤️

Well our first time Burbot fishing was a success! Using a @jsoutfitter Custom Walleye Wacker, a Northland Coffin spoon, and a bunch of minnow chunks I was able to pull multiple fish topside! These fish are honestly incredible and using a camera to watch them made the experience even more fun! 

We ended up keeping a handful that we cooked up last night, I now understand why people refer to them as poor man’s lobster! 😍

Battle on Bago is an ice fishing event that I look forward to ever February. I’ve honestly been doing this tournament now since 2013, with only one missed year when it was cancelled due to poor ice conditions.  This is by far the best run tournament I’ve participated it with some incredible sponsors! 

We started our weekend on Lake Poygan but couldn’t find a good bite so we grabbed some Culver’s and headed to Lake Winnebago. Unfortunately for me I was on the struggle bus but Trevor came in clutch and was able to catch a nice whitebass we were able to register.  We packed up our gear and prepared for day 2…. 

(Edit- this fish was caught the week prior to the tournament 😂)

Day 2 - We headed back to Lake Winnebago in hopes we could fill our last 3 tickets. We grinded it out and we’re able to pull another whitebass, and quite a few quality perch!  In the end our fish made the top 2000, however, none landed us on any prizes…But you can bet next year I’ll be coming back for the truck or the boat 😉

If you ever have the pleasure of visiting Oshkosh Wisconsin for Battle on Bago, make sure to stop in for dinner at @theroxyoshkosh  and  @leons_oshkosh for dessert! 

(Note- photo was taken the week prior to Battle on Bago on Lake Winnebago) 

Cheers! 🍻

Phillips Chain of Lakes in Phillips Wisconsin was the absolutely perfect place to spend our opener…Fish were caught, good times were had, and memories were made!

We stopped at Ross's Sport Shop and Guide Service right in town for bait and advice, with that in hand we set out the next morning bright and early….We caught fish on everything from a jig and a minnow, to plastics, and crank baits. 

If you find yourself in the area do yourself a favor and take a trip over to the St. Croix Rods Store in Park Falls for a tour and maybe a little shopping spree… honestly I’m surprised I didn’t come home broke 😂

We may not have come home with limits, but we came home with plenty of fish stories to tell 😉

I hope you all had a wonderful Fishing Opener! A special thanks to Phillips Area Chamber of Commerce  and Park Falls Area Chamber of Commerce for the hospitality, and Up North Vacation Lodging for the amazing accommodations! We’re already looking forward to next year 😃

Phillips & Park Fall Check list
✅Timms Hill -highest point in Wisconsin 
✅Ross’s Bait- everything a fishermen could ever need! 
✅Fish the Phillips Chain 
✅Smiths Covered Bridge- 1 of only 2 lattice bridges in Wisconsin 
✅St. Croix Rods Tour 
✅Cocktails and Games at Nemo’s bar 
✅Dinner at Birch Resort

Friendly PSA- Whitebass are running on the Wolf River! 

These fish are such a blast to catch, with the warm temperatures they should be pushing shallow making spinnerbaits an optimal choice! I personally love pulling a Wolf-River rig with a fly set about a minnow for chances at doubles! 

Good Luck and Tight Lines!

Getting ready for the Wisconsin Gun Opener tomorrow! 🧡

Good luck to all my fellow hunters hitting the woods, stay safe and know your target! 

And for the love of all things holy, don’t shoot an elk 😂

20+ years of memories in the Wisconsin woods: where family, friends, and deer tales intersect in the grand tradition of the gun deer opener. So many incredible memories with past and present hunters that have become some of my most cherished memories. To keep the tradition alive please always remember to practice TABK. 

-Treat every 🔫 like it’s loaded
-Always point the muzzle in a safe direction
-Be Target Savvy- know your target and what is beyond it
-Keep that trigger finger on vacation until it’s showtime!

I’ll be hitting the woods all weekend in hopes to fill my tag! Good luck to everyone getting out!🧡
